<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA512FFB568EDBC7DCF1AFD97" blockId="7.[915,1352,552,574]" box="[915,1352,552,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">
<heading id="D0ACF863A512FFB568EDBC7DCF1AFD97" box="[915,1352,552,574]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" reason="8">
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB568EDBC7DCF1AFD97" authority="NAYAR, 1968" authorityName="Nayar" authorityYear="1968" box="[915,1352,552,574]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB568EDBC7DCEF5FD95" box="[915,1191,552,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">XANTHOGRAMMA INDICA</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA512FFB56FCFBC7DCF1AFD97" author="Nayar JL" box="[1201,1352,552,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" pagination="121 - 131" refId="ref56016" refString="Nayar JL. 1968. A contribution to our knowledge of high altitude Syrphidae (Cyclorrhapha: Diptera) from N. W. Himalaya. Part I - subfamily Syrphinae. Agra University Journal of Research Science [1967] 16: 121 - 131." type="journal article" year="1968">NAYAR, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA512FFB56844BC1ACEF2FBC5" blockId="7.[826,1441,590,1285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA512FFB56844BC1AC98BFDCD" author="Nayar JL" box="[826,985,590,612]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" pagination="121 - 131" refId="ref56016" refString="Nayar JL. 1968. A contribution to our knowledge of high altitude Syrphidae (Cyclorrhapha: Diptera) from N. W. Himalaya. Part I - subfamily Syrphinae. Agra University Journal of Research Science [1967] 16: 121 - 131." type="journal article" year="1968">Nayar (1968)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species from 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA512FFB56E1ABC1BCFF3FDCD" box="[1380,1441,590,612]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">India</collectingCountry>
based on a single female from Kalatop, Dalhousie (
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA512FFB5683CBCDEC9D0FD08" box="[834,898,651,673]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">India</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="499F81EDA512FFB568F3BCDECE30FD08" box="[909,1122,651,673]" country="India" name="Himachal Pradesh" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Himachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
) and mentioned that it was similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB568C6BCFECEE2FD69" authority="Brunettii" authorityName="Brunettii" box="[952,1200,682,704]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinum">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB568C6BCFECE68FD69" box="[952,1082,683,704]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">X. citrinum</emphasis>
Brunettii
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56FA9BCFFC9D3FD77" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrinum">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56FA9BCFFC9D3FD77" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Citrogramma citrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on his original description, this species can be separated from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56FC3BCBDCF05FD54" box="[1213,1367,744,765]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56FC3BCBDCF05FD54" box="[1213,1367,744,765]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Citrogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on abdominal pattern, with terga 3 and 4 with two lateral curved yellow maculae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56FE1BD71CFF3FC90" authorityName="Nayar" authorityYear="1968" box="[1183,1441,804,825]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56FE1BD71CFF3FC90" box="[1183,1441,804,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Xanthogramma indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56812BD11C989FCF1" authorityName="Deoras" authorityYear="1942" box="[876,987,835,857]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruthii">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56812BD11C989FCF1" box="[876,987,835,857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">X. pruthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are both described from northern 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA512FFB56E1ABD16CFF3FCF0" box="[1380,1441,835,857]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">India</collectingCountry>
and they share a similar abdominal and mesonotal pattern, medial black facial vitta, frons, leg colour pattern, and pleural pattern. Hence 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56E7FBDF5CF3AFC1D" authorityName="Nayar" authorityYear="1968" box="[1281,1384,927,949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56E7FBDF5CF3AFC1D" box="[1281,1384,927,949]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">X. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56844BDEBC9FBFC7B" authorityName="Deoras" authorityYear="1942" box="[826,937,957,979]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruthii">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56844BDEBC9FBFC7B" box="[826,937,957,979]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">X. pruthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be the same species. This argument was corroborated by Ghorpadé (unpubl. data), who studied the 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA512FFB568B8BDAEC9A5FBB9" box="[966,1015,1019,1040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
material at the Zoological Survey of 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA512FFB56844BA4CC925FB86" box="[826,887,1049,1071]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">India</collectingCountry>
(NZSI, Calcutta) and synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56E1ABA4FC9E4FBE4" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Scaeva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latimaculata">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56E1ABA4FC9E4FBE4" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">S. latimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after examining the 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA512FFB56FD9BA6DCE8AFBE4" box="[1191,1240,1080,1101]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56E1ABA6DC9E4FBC2" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Scaeva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latimaculata">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56E1ABA6DC9E4FBC2" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">S. latimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at BMNH, London.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3411C84A512FFB5682DBA20C9C6FAAC" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA512FFB5682DBA20C9C6FAAC" blockId="7.[826,1441,590,1285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">
Thus, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56F6EBA20CE91FB23" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1860" box="[1040,1219,1141,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56F6EBA20CE91FB23" box="[1040,1219,1141,1162]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Xanthogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not so far been found in the Oriental Region, except for 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA512FFB56E38BAC1CEEBFB6E" authority="Shiraki, 1930" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xanthogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanum">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA512FFB56E38BAC1CE40FB61" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">Xanthogramma coreanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA512FFB56F65BAE7CEEBFB6E" author="Shiraki T" box="[1051,1209,1202,1224]" pageId="7" pageNumber="106" refId="ref56243" refString="Shiraki T. 1930. Die Syrphiden des Japanischen Kaiserreiches mit Berucksichtigung benachbarter Gebiete. Memoirs of the Faculty of Science and Agriculture Taihoku Imperial University 1." type="journal volume" year="1930">Shiraki, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, taken in some Oriental Provinces of southern 
<collectingCountry id="F34C0F9FA512FFB56F05BA84CE92FB4E" box="[1147,1216,1233,1255]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="106">China</collectingCountry>
(K. Ghorpadé pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
